  </div>
</nav>

<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span>Interactive · 60 seconds · 6 questions</div>
    <h1 class="hero-h">Should I use Claude <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">or ChatGPT?</em></h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">
      A short decision tool calibrated to your business needs. Answer 6 questions; get back a specific recommendation with reasoning. Most teams should use both for different jobs — this tool tells you which one for which job, based on your situation.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <div class="quiz">
      <div class="progress" id="progress">
        <div class="dot active"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="q active" data-q="0">
        <h3>What's the primary use case you're thinking about?</h3>
        <div class="opts">
          <button class="opt" data-val="writing">Long-form writing (proposals, content, reports)</button>
          <button class="opt" data-val="quick">Quick everyday assists (email drafts, summaries, brainstorming)</button>
          <button class="opt" data-val="coding">Coding / technical work</button>
          <button class="opt" data-val="research">Research and analysis</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q" data-q="1">
        <h3>How many people will use the tool?</h3>
        <div class="opts">
          <button class="opt" data-val="solo">Just me (1)</button>
          <button class="opt" data-val="small">Small team (2–10)</button>
          <button class="opt" data-val="medium">Mid-size team (10–50)</button>
          <button class="opt" data-val="large">Larger org (50+)</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q" data-q="2">
        <h3>Do you need a shared knowledge base (your docs, ICP, brand voice loaded once for the team)?</h3>
        <div class="opts">
          <button class="opt" data-val="critical">Yes — critical for the workflow</button>
          <button class="opt" data-val="nice">Nice to have</button>
          <button class="opt" data-val="no">No, individual use is fine</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q" data-q="3">
        <h3>Do you need access to a marketplace of pre-built specialized tools (GPTs)?</h3>
        <div class="opts">
          <button class="opt" data-val="yes">Yes — useful for variety of tasks</button>
          <button class="opt" data-val="no">No — I prefer building my own setup</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q" data-q="4">
        <h3>Is sustained output quality more important than ecosystem breadth?</h3>
        <div class="opts">
          <button class="opt" data-val="quality">Quality matters most — especially for client-facing output</button>
          <button class="opt" data-val="breadth">Breadth matters more — many small tasks across various needs</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q" data-q="5">
        <h3>Do you have specific compliance requirements (HIPAA, FedRAMP, EU data residency)?</h3>
        <div class="opts">
          <button class="opt" data-val="yes">Yes — formal requirements</button>
          <button class="opt" data-val="no">No</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="result" id="result">
        <div class="result-h" id="result-headline">Claude (Team plan)</div>
        <div class="result-p" id="result-body"></div>
        <div class="result-detail" id="result-detail"></div>
        <div class="result-actions">
          <button class="btn-g" onclick="window.location.reload()">Restart quiz</button>
          <a href="/chatgpt-vs-claude-for-business" class="btn-p">Read the full comparison →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="nav-row" id="navrow">
        <button class="btn-g" id="back" style="visibility:hidden">← Back</button>
        <span id="qcount" style="color:#8FAF8F;font-size:0.85rem;align-self:center;">Question 1 of 6</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">More on the decision</span>
    <h2 class="h2">Read deeper</h2>
    <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;color:#C0D8C0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.85;">
      <li style="padding:0.5rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;"><a href="/chatgpt-vs-claude-for-business" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">Claude vs ChatGPT for business (full comparison) →</a></li>
      <li style="padding:0.5rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;"><a href="/how-much-does-claude-cost-for-business" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">How much does Claude cost for business? →</a></li>
      <li style="padding:0.5rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;"><a href="/claude-vs-perplexity-for-business" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">Claude vs Perplexity for business →</a></li>
      <li style="padding:0.5rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;"><a href="/claude-team-vs-claude-enterprise" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">Claude Team vs Claude Enterprise →</a></li>
      <li style="padding:0.5rem 0;"><a href="/what-is-claude-projects" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">What is Claude Projects? →</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <div class="cta-box">
      <div>
        <div class="cta-text">Need help picking your full AI stack?</div>
        <div class="cta-sub">The $1,500 AI Audit gives you a written tool-stack recommendation for your specific workflows.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <a href="/services/ai-audit" class="btn-p">Book the AI Audit →</a>
        <a href="/quiz" class="btn-g">Take the Gap Assessment</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- treetop-linker-related-START -->
<section style="padding:3.5rem 2.5rem;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;background:#050D05;">
  <div style="max-width:780px;margin:0 auto;">
    <span style="font-size:0.68rem;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#00C853;margin-bottom:0.75rem;display:block;">Related</span>
    <h2 style="font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;font-size:clamp(1.5rem,2.8vw,2rem);font-weight:400;line-height:1.2;color:#F0FFF0;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Explore more from Treetop</h2>
    <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;font-size:0.96rem;line-height:1.9;color:#C0D8C0;">
    <li><a href="/fractional-cmo" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,200,83,0.3);">What a fractional CMO does &rarr;</a></li>
    <li><a href="/ai-for-cmos" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,200,83,0.3);">The AI toolkit for marketing leaders &rarr;</a></li>
    <li><a href="/the-ai-native-gtm-framework" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,200,83,0.3);">Treetop's AI-native GTM framework &rarr;</a></li>
    <li><a href="/what-is-ai-native-gtm" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,200,83,0.3);">AI-native GTM, defined &rarr;</a></li>
    <li><a href="/how-to-use-ai-in-your-business" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,200,83,0.3);">How to roll out AI in your business &rarr;</a></li>
    <li><a href="/glossary" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,200,83,0.3);">Treetop's glossary &rarr;</a></li>
    <li><a href="/resources" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,200,83,0.3);">Resource library &rarr;</a></li>
    <li><a href="/claude-for-small-business" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,200,83,0.3);">Practical Claude for small business &rarr;</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>
<!-- treetop-linker-related-END -->

<GlobalFooter />

<script is:inline>
  (function() {
    var answers = {};
    var current = 0;
    var total = 6;

    function updateProgress() {
      var dots = document.querySelectorAll('#progress .dot');
      dots.forEach(function(d, i) {
        d.classList.remove('active', 'done');
        if (i < current) d.classList.add('done');
        if (i === current) d.classList.add('active');
      });
      document.getElementById('qcount').textContent = 'Question ' + (current + 1) + ' of ' + total;
      document.getElementById('back').style.visibility = current > 0 ? 'visible' : 'hidden';
    }

    function showQuestion(idx) {
      document.querySelectorAll('.q').forEach(function(q) { q.classList.remove('active'); });
      var q = document.querySelector('[data-q="' + idx + '"]');
      if (q) q.classList.add('active');
      current = idx;
      updateProgress();
    }

    document.querySelectorAll('.opt').forEach(function(btn) {
      btn.addEventListener('click', function() {
        var q = parseInt(btn.closest('.q').dataset.q, 10);
        answers[q] = btn.dataset.val;
        if (q < total - 1) {
          setTimeout(function() { showQuestion(q + 1); }, 150);
        } else {
          setTimeout(showResult, 200);
        }
      });
    });

    document.getElementById('back').addEventListener('click', function() {
      if (current > 0) showQuestion(current - 1);
    });

    function showResult() {
      // Hide questions
      document.querySelectorAll('.q').forEach(function(q) { q.classList.remove('active'); });
      document.getElementById('navrow').style.display = 'none';
      document.querySelectorAll('#progress .dot').forEach(function(d) { d.classList.add('done'); d.classList.remove('active'); });

      // Scoring
      var claudeScore = 0;
      var chatgptScore = 0;
      var bothScore = 0;

      // Q0: use case
      if (answers[0] === 'writing') claudeScore += 3;
      if (answers[0] === 'quick') chatgptScore += 1;
      if (answers[0] === 'coding') claudeScore += 3;
      if (answers[0] === 'research') { claudeScore += 2; bothScore += 1; }

      // Q1: team size
      if (answers[1] === 'medium' || answers[1] === 'large') claudeScore += 2;
      if (answers[1] === 'solo' || answers[1] === 'small') bothScore += 1;

      // Q2: shared knowledge
      if (answers[2] === 'critical') claudeScore += 3;
      if (answers[2] === 'nice') claudeScore += 1;

      // Q3: GPT marketplace
      if (answers[3] === 'yes') chatgptScore += 2;
      if (answers[3] === 'no') claudeScore += 1;

      // Q4: quality vs breadth
      if (answers[4] === 'quality') claudeScore += 2;
      if (answers[4] === 'breadth') { chatgptScore += 2; bothScore += 1; }

      // Q5: compliance
      if (answers[5] === 'yes') claudeScore += 2;

      // Determine recommendation
      var rec, headline, body, detail;
      if (claudeScore > chatgptScore + 2) {
        rec = 'claude';
      } else if (chatgptScore > claudeScore + 2) {
        rec = 'chatgpt';
      } else {
        rec = 'both';
      }

      var planTier;
      if (answers[1] === 'solo') planTier = 'Pro ($20/mo)';
      else if (answers[1] === 'large' || answers[5] === 'yes') planTier = 'Enterprise';
      else planTier = 'Team ($30/seat/mo)';

      if (rec === 'claude') {
        headline = 'Claude — ' + planTier;
        body = '<strong>Claude is the right primary choice for your situation.</strong> The combination of factors you described (especially the writing focus, team size, and shared knowledge needs) maps well to what Claude does best. ChatGPT would be a step down for these specific workflows.';
        detail = '<p><strong>Why Claude wins for you:</strong> Long-form writing quality is best in class. Shared Projects let your team operate against the same ICP, voice, and proof points. Strong instruction-following for production workflows. Best-in-class coding capability if that\'s in your scope.</p>';
      } else if (rec === 'chatgpt') {
        headline = 'ChatGPT — Team or Plus';
        body = '<strong>ChatGPT is the better fit for your specific use case.</strong> Your needs are more about variety and breadth than about sustained workflows or team-wide consistency. The GPT marketplace gives you specialized tools across many small jobs.';
        detail = '<p><strong>Why ChatGPT wins for you:</strong> Broader marketplace of pre-built GPTs. Faster for short queries. Better for quick everyday assists. Plenty good enough for individual or small-team use where each person can build their own workflow.</p>';
      } else {
        headline = 'Use both — different tools for different jobs';
        body = '<strong>Your needs cross both tools.</strong> Smart teams in your situation use Claude as the primary workhorse for sustained workflows + customer-facing output, plus ChatGPT for breadth and specialized GPT marketplace use cases.';
        detail = '<p><strong>The recommended split:</strong> Claude Team ($30/seat) as your primary deployment. ChatGPT Plus ($20/mo) on the side for the 2-3 people who do significant variety of tasks. Total combined cost is comparable to one mid-tier SaaS subscription. Combined output is meaningfully higher than either alone.</p>';
      }

      document.getElementById('result-headline').textContent = headline;
      document.getElementById('result-body').innerHTML = body;
      document.getElementById('result-detail').innerHTML = detail;
      document.getElementById('result').classList.add('active');
    }

    updateProgress();
  })();
</script>

</body>
</html>
